title Defence Intelligence Landscape (March 2023)
style wardley

// Anchors: primary decision-maker plus oversight / citizen stakeholders
anchor Military Command [0.97, 0.75]
anchor Government [0.95, 0.65]
anchor Citizens [0.93, 0.55]

// Decision layer
component Operational Decisions [0.87, 0.58]
component Intelligence Agencies [0.82, 0.68]
component Decision Model (HITL/HOTL) [0.78, 0.28]
component Trust (Competence/Integrity/Benevolence) [0.70, 0.18]

// Analysis layer
component Intelligence Analysis [0.68, 0.45] inertia
component Target Discovery [0.60, 0.55]
component AI/ML Analytics Engine [0.52, 0.32]
component Intelligence Collection [0.50, 0.58]

// Source layer
component Verified Diverse Sources [0.42, 0.50]
component Regulation, Privacy & Ownership [0.40, 0.35]
component OSINT [0.35, 0.68]
component Social Media & Crowdsourcing [0.28, 0.62]
component Adversarial Capability [0.28, 0.22]
component Sensors (GPS/Cameras/Signals) [0.22, 0.82]

// Dependencies — value chain from anchors down to sources
Military Command->Operational Decisions
Military Command->Intelligence Agencies
Government->Operational Decisions
Government->Regulation, Privacy & Ownership
Citizens->Regulation, Privacy & Ownership

Operational Decisions->Decision Model (HITL/HOTL)
Operational Decisions->Intelligence Analysis
Intelligence Agencies->Intelligence Analysis
Intelligence Agencies->Target Discovery

Decision Model (HITL/HOTL)->Trust (Competence/Integrity/Benevolence)
Decision Model (HITL/HOTL)->AI/ML Analytics Engine

Intelligence Analysis->AI/ML Analytics Engine
Intelligence Analysis->Verified Diverse Sources
Target Discovery->Intelligence Collection
Intelligence Collection->Verified Diverse Sources
AI/ML Analytics Engine->Verified Diverse Sources

Verified Diverse Sources->OSINT
Verified Diverse Sources->Social Media & Crowdsourcing
Verified Diverse Sources->Sensors (GPS/Cameras/Signals)
OSINT->Social Media & Crowdsourcing

// Regulation constrains public-data sources and sensor use
Regulation, Privacy & Ownership->OSINT
Regulation, Privacy & Ownership->Social Media & Crowdsourcing
Regulation, Privacy & Ownership->Sensors (GPS/Cameras/Signals)

// Adversary contaminates crowd-sourced streams and targets the AI layer
Social Media & Crowdsourcing->Adversarial Capability
AI/ML Analytics Engine->Adversarial Capability

// Evolution arrows (predicted 12-24 month movement)
evolve AI/ML Analytics Engine 0.55
evolve Decision Model (HITL/HOTL) 0.45
evolve Trust (Competence/Integrity/Benevolence) 0.32
evolve Adversarial Capability 0.42
evolve Regulation, Privacy & Ownership 0.50
evolve OSINT 0.78

// Inertia marker above captures legacy tradecraft resistance to AI-native workflows

annotation 1 [[0.30, 0.30]] Bleeding-edge zone: LLM-era analytics, HITL/HOTL doctrine, prompt-injection threat
annotation 2 [[0.20, 0.82]] Commoditised: GPS, cameras, network signals are utility inputs
annotation 3 [[0.42, 0.68]] OSINT tooling maturing toward commodity utility
